A letter from His Holiness the Pope of Rome, to His Highness the Prince of Orange containing several proposals and overtures of agreement betwixt the Church of England, and the Church of Rome / translated out of Latin, for the benefit of all true Protestants. Innocent XI, Pope, 1611-1689. William III, King of England, 1650-1702.
8 p.
[s.n.], Reprinted at Edinburgh : 1689.
"A pretended letter." -- Editor's note. "The Church of England's answer to the preceding letter": p. 7. Reproduction of original in Huntington Library.
